25/02/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police on Thursday (February 24th) searched three locations for information that could lead them to war crimes fugitive Goran Hadzic. Interior Minister Ivica Dacic says the raids, conducted northwest of Belgrade, had police looking for documents or other information resulting in Hadzic's arrest. No other details were revealed. (B92, Beta, RTS, Pink TV, Dnevnik, Vecernje Novosti, Mondo, Blic - 24/02/11)
